rComments: Professor Salole is a very good lecturer - clear, concise and passionate about the subject matter. She has inspired me to further pursue the plight of young people in conflict with the law. Attending class is key however as she expands well on the reading materials. An incredibly nice person as well!
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Inspirational', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: This was one of the best courses I've taken at U of T. Theoretical and applied. She lined up some awesome guest speakers and she seems to know what's actually happening with young offenders around here. I would take another course with her even though she's tough.

She's a decent prof. Smart and good at her job. But she is literally an amazing person. Prof. Salole is funny, clever and caring. Take the course! And also make sure she knows who you are. She's just a good person to know.

I think I learned the most from office hours. She's just smart.   You have to read and show up for lecture. She's a gem of a person and appears to care about students. She gave me an extension and lots of personal attention and I got a 90 on the essay. Its not an easy course,
Love this Professor! Awesome course - make sure to attend lectures!

I really enjoyed the class. She did her best to make the class exciting. She's very passionate and takes the time to explain the material. Documentaries, podcasts etc. She knows her material well. I wish she taught more courses.

Although I respect Professor Salole as a person, she seems very kind and has great knowledge of her topic, I did not like her lecture style. The class itself was not hard but the lectures very very dry and monotone. At the same time to get a good grade you need to attend lectures because the essay questions are mainly lecture based.

I love Abigail Salole, she is the best sociology professor I've had in a while. She really cares for her students, and shows it by giving you her full attention when you talk to her. She is so sweet during office hours and will help you the best she can. Oh, she is also very beautiful and good to look at, so I never missed a single lecture : )
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Thats my homegirl yo! She's an amazing prof. Her lectures are really enjoyable and is always there for her students

She gives you some of the questions for the midterm and and exam. The other questions are no surprise if you attend lecture and understand the themes you'll be fine. Her tests are all based on lectures, don't even need the textbook. To do well: the questions are broad, make sure to apply concepts like: intersectionality and etc.

Prof Salole is awesome would definately recommend the course to others unless you are one to skip class. She makes you want to go to the lectures by showing videos and current life situations to relate course concepts.
My fav prof at UTM. Down to earth, smart, and really nice. Cool course.
A bit different from most profs - in a good way. Knows her stuff!
Prof Salole is one of the nicest profs I know. She really cares and it shows. Great course.

one of the worst i had at this school. i dropped it quick. when u visit office hours she IS SO VAGUE at explaining papers. her course outlines were all mixed up with criteria for future papers so u ALWAYS need clarification. almost all the people i knew who took the class dropped it or did creditno credit. lectures DON'T match tests, IT'S HARD!
